      "content": "i get the urgency, but you're kind of framing it like there isn't really any other choice. people argue that things like massive solar and wind scale-ups, plus better battery storage, are just as viable solutions without the whole nuclear baggage. isn't it more accurate to say nuclear is just one competing option among several, rather than saying it's a necessity because of the climate crisis?",
